<subSubSection id="D3E79686FFF8FFBBFF9356BFA4C7FD2E" pageId="7" pageNumber="924" type="description">
<paragraph id="9B42C50DFFF8FFBBFF9356BFA4D8FF30" blockId="7.[111,648,216,750]" box="[113,412,216,242]" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">
DESCRIPTION OF 
<typeStatus id="44467BAFFFF8FFBBFECF56BAA4D8FF30" box="[301,412,221,240]" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9B42C50DFFF8FFBBFF93569FA77EFD0E" blockId="7.[111,648,216,750]" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">
Length: 
<quantity id="5C0568E8FFF8FFBBFF29569FA460FED3" box="[203,292,248,275]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="924" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
; length of elytra: 
<quantity id="5C0568E8FFF8FFBBFE3C569FA772FED3" box="[478,566,248,275]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="924" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
; width: 
<quantity id="5C0568E8FFF8FFBBFF935770A595FEF2" box="[113,209,279,306]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="924" unit="mm" value="3.8">3.8 mm</quantity>
. Body surface dark green with greenish shine, partly reddish. Head as in 
<taxonomicName id="5CFDBE8EFFF8FFBBFDE0575FA73BFE91" baseAuthorityName="Blanchard" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[514,639,311,337]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Heptomera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="924" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="A989191FFFF8FFBBFDE0575FA73BFE91" box="[514,639,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">E. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; ocular canthus without terminal setae. Eyes, ratio of diameter/interocular width: 0.63. Antennomeres 3-5 fused; antennal club 1.5 times longer than the remaining antennomeres combined. Pronotum and scutellum as in 
<taxonomicName id="5CFDBE8EFFF8FFBBFEF357B1A4CEFE2F" baseAuthorityName="Blanchard" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[273,394,469,495]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Heptomera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="924" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="A989191FFFF8FFBBFEF357B1A4CEFE2F" box="[273,394,469,495]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">E. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Elytra as in 
<taxonomicName id="5CFDBE8EFFF8FFBBFDEC57B1A7C3FE2F" baseAuthorityName="Blanchard" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[526,647,469,495]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Heptomera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="924" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="A989191FFFF8FFBBFDEC57B1A7C3FE2F" box="[526,647,469,495]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">E. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but without convex semicircular declivity, apical interior angle convex, apical external angle oblique, and apical border convex. Metacoxa and pygidium as in 
<taxonomicName id="5CFDBE8EFFF8FFBBFF4A5432A467FDAE" baseAuthorityName="Blanchard" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[168,291,596,622]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Heptomera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="924" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="A989191FFFF8FFBBFF4A5432A467FDAE" box="[168,291,596,622]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">E. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; tooth of posterior external angle of metacoxa moderately sharp. Ratio of length of metepisternum/metacoxa:1/2.0. Legs as in 
<taxonomicName id="5CFDBE8EFFF8FFBBFDCE54F3A5D2FD0D" baseAuthorityName="Blanchard" baseAuthorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Heptomera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="924" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="A989191FFFF8FFBBFDCE54F3A5D2FD0D" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">E.metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; posterior legs lacking in the 
<typeStatus id="44467BAFFFF8FFBBFE3654D4A772FD0E" box="[468,566,691,718]" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9B42C50DFFF8FFBBFF6A54B4A4C7FD2E" blockId="7.[111,648,216,750]" box="[136,387,723,750]" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">
Aedeagus: 
<figureCitation id="03C6D988FFF8FFBBFF1954B4A410FD2E" box="[251,340,723,750]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[113,124,1612,1629]" captionTargetBox="[186,1133,716,1585]" captionTargetId="figure-229@8.[184,660,1124,1495]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 2. — A-C, Emphania nitida Moser, 1911 (lectotype); D-F, E. sulcipennis Moser, 1911 (Madagascar Nord, Montagne d’Ambre); G-I, E. semiviridis n. sp. (holotype); J-L, E. erichsoni n. sp. (holotype); M-O, E. subsmaragdina n. sp. (holotype); P-R, E. ranomafanae n. sp. (holotype); A, D, G, J, M, P, aedeagus,left side lateral views;B, E, H, K, N, Q, aedeagus,dorsal views;C, F, I, L, O, R, aedeagus, right side lateral views. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4525867" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4525867/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">Figure 2</figureCitation>
G-I.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D3E79686FFF8FFBBFF935574A4B4FBEB" pageId="7" pageNumber="924" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9B42C50DFFF8FFBBFF935574A591FCEB" blockId="7.[111,648,787,1067]" box="[113,213,787,813]" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9B42C50DFFF8FFBBFF935555A4B4FBEB" blockId="7.[111,648,787,1067]" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">
The species shares the fused antennomeres 3-5 with the similar 
<taxonomicName id="5CFDBE8EFFF8FFBBFF045535A41BFCAB" baseAuthorityName="Blanchard" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[230,351,849,875]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Heptomera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="924" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="A989191FFFF8FFBBFF045535A41BFCAB" box="[230,351,849,875]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">E. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="5CFDBE8EFFF8FFBBFE895536A70DFCAB" authority="Ahrens &amp; Fabrizi, 2008" authorityName="Ahrens &amp; Fabrizi" authorityYear="2008" box="[363,585,849,875]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Emphania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="924" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semiviridis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="A989191FFFF8FFBBFE895536A70DFCAB" box="[363,585,849,875]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">Emphania semiviridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="B2BAA464FFF8FFBBFDAC5536A7C3FCAC" box="[590,647,849,876]" pageId="7" pageNumber="924" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="5CFDBE8EFFF8FFBBFF0D5515A421FC4B" baseAuthorityName="Blanchard" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[239,357,881,907]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Heptomera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="924" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="A989191FFFF8FFBBFF0D5515A421FC4B" box="[239,357,881,907]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="924">E. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the smaller body size, the lacking posterior elytral declivity, the longer antennal club being 1.5 times longer than the remaining antennomeres combined, and the shape of male genitalia having the distinctly shorter parameres with a sharply pointed apical hook.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
